Accor, Areva, Bongrain, Iliad, Schneider: French Equity Preview

-- B y   M a r k   D e e n
-- 
2011-07-22T04:00:01Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-07-21/accor-areva-bongrain-iliad-schneider-french-equity-preview.html
The following is a list of companies
whose stocks may have unusual price changes in Paris. Symbols
are in parentheses after company names and prices are from the
last close.  France ’s  CAC 40 Index (CAC)  rose 1.7 percent to 3,816.75.  Accor SA (AC)  : The hotel company said it is negotiating
the possible sale of Lenotre to Sodexho. Lenotre has an
enterprise value of 75 million euros ($108 million), Accor said.
The shares climbed 1.1 percent to 30.63 euros.  Areva SA (AREVA FP): The power station builder may be
behind schedule in building its Finnish nuclear power plant,
Greenpeace said, citing  Finland ’s nuclear authority. The shares
rose 1.3 percent to 24.22 euros.  Bongrain SA (BH)  : The dairy company said first-half
revenue rose 13.2 percent to 1.88 billion euros from 1.66
billion euros in the same period last year. The shares rose 2.7
percent to 64.17 euros.  Iliad SA (ILD)  : The telephone services company said it
completed an accord with France Telecom SA to co-finance fiber-
optic networks in France. The deal will cover about five million
homes. The shares climbed 1.6 percent to 90.13 euros.  Pierre & Vacances (VAC)  SA: The vacation apartments
company said third-quarter revenue rose 11 percent to 319
million euros. The company said it sees “significant” growth
in sales in the fiscal year ending September. The shares were
unchanged at 58.02 euros.  Schneider Electric SA (SU)  : The electrical products
company said it agreed to a partnership with NVC Lighting
Holding Ltd. to expand its distribution network in smaller
Chinese cities. Schneider will acquire a 9.2 percent stake in
the Guangdong, China-based NVC Lighting. The stock gained 0.1
percent to 105.95 euros.  To contact the reporters on this story:
Mark Deen in Paris at 
 markdeen@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
